radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is distended up to 1.4 cm thick with adjacent fatty stranding consistent with acute appendicitis. No drainable collection or abscess. No focal liver lesion, no intrahepatic or extrahepatic ductal dilation, and all other abdominal and pelvic organs are unremarkable. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. There is mild moderate compression at L3 of indeterminate age, possibly chronic with degenerative changes at adjacent L2-3 level.
